<h2 class="chapter">4 Citations</h2>

<p><a name="index-Citations-184"></a><a name="index-g_t_0040code_007b_005ccite_007d-185"></a>
Citations in LaTeX are done with the <code>\cite</code> macro or variations of
it.  The argument of the macro is a citation key which identifies an
article or book in either a BibTeX database file or in an explicit
<code>thebibliography</code> environment in the document.  RefTeX's
support for citations helps to select the correct key quickly.

<ul class="menu">
<li><a accesskey="1" href="#Creating-Citations">Creating Citations</a>:                How to create them. 
