<h3 class="section">4.5 Citations outside LaTeX</h3>

<p><a name="index-Citations-outside-LaTeX-223"></a><a name="index-reftex_002ddefault_002dbibliography-224"></a>
The command <code>reftex-citation</code> can also be executed outside a LaTeX
buffer.  This can be useful to reference articles in the mail buffer and
other documents.  You should <em>not</em> enter <code>reftex-mode</code> for
this, just execute the command.  The list of BibTeX files will in this
case be taken from the variable <code>reftex-default-bibliography</code>. 
Setting the variable <code>reftex-cite-format</code> to the symbol
<code>locally</code> does a decent job of putting all relevant information
about a citation directly into the buffer.  Here is the lisp code to add
the <kbd>C-c [</kbd> binding to the mail buffer.  It also provides a local
binding for <code>reftex-cite-format</code>.

<pre class="lisp">     (add-hook 'mail-setup-hook
               (lambda () (define-key mail-mode-map "\C-c["
                            (lambda ()
                              (interactive)
                              (let ((reftex-cite-format 'locally))
                                (reftex-citation))))))
</pre>
