<h2 class="chapter">9 Faces</h2>

<p><a name="index-Faces-311"></a>
RefTeX uses faces when available to structure the selection and
table of contents buffers.  It does not create its own faces, but uses
the ones defined in <samp><span class="file">font-lock.el</span></samp>.  Therefore, RefTeX will
use faces only when <code>font-lock</code> is loaded.  This seems to be
reasonable because people who like faces will very likely have it
loaded.  If you wish to turn off fontification or change the involved
faces, see <a href="#Options-_002d-Fontification">Options - Fontification</a>.

