<h3 class="section">18.12 Keymaps and Hooks</h3>

<p><a name="index-Keymaps-582"></a>
RefTeX has the usual general keymap, load hook and mode hook.

<div class="defun">
&mdash; Keymap: <b>reftex-mode-map</b><var><a name="index-reftex_002dmode_002dmap-583"></a></var><br>
<blockquote><p>The keymap for RefTeX mode. 
</p></blockquote></div>

<div class="defun">
&mdash; Normal Hook: <b>reftex-load-hook</b><var><a name="index-reftex_002dload_002dhook-584"></a></var><br>
<blockquote><p>Normal hook which is being run when loading <samp><span class="file">reftex.el</span></samp>. 
</p></blockquote></div>

<div class="defun">
&mdash; Normal Hook: <b>reftex-mode-hook</b><var><a name="index-reftex_002dmode_002dhook-585"></a></var><br>
<blockquote><p>Normal hook which is being run when turning on RefTeX mode. 
</p></blockquote></div>

   <p>Furthermore, the four modes used for referencing labels, creating
citations, the table of contents buffer and the phrases buffer have
their own keymaps and mode hooks.  See the respective sections.  There
are many more hooks which are described in the relevant sections about
options for a specific part of RefTeX.

